<title>USA: Spectrian sells unit to employees.</title>
<headline>Spectrian sells unit to employees.</headline>
<dateline>SUNNYVALE, Calif. 1997-04-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Spectrian Corp said Thursday it has sold its American Microwave Technology unit to a group of employees.</p>
<p>AMT, which was acquired by Spectrian in 1987, specializes in amplifiers for medical, scientific and application-specific markets. Terms of the deal were not disclosed.</p>
<p>Spectrian said it decided to divest AMT becasue it's market focus has become less synergistic with Spectrian's core business.</p>
